  "prompt": "How do my family and I Live in tijuana for one month?",
  "response": "To live in Tijuana for one month, consider these steps:\n\n1. Housing\n- Rent a furnished apartment or Airbnb\n- Look for areas like Zona Rio, Playas de Tijuana, or Hidalgo\n- Budget around $500-$1500 per month depending on location/amenities\n\n2. Visa/Legal Requirements\n- US citizens can stay up to 180 days with a tourist permit\n- Get a tourist permit at the border or online\n- Ensure passports are valid\n\n3. Finances\n- Bring sufficient cash or credit cards\n- Exchange some money to pesos\n- Inform bank about travel to avoid card issues\n\n4. Transportation\n- Consider renting a car\n- Use local taxis or ride-sharing apps\n- Public transportation is available\n\n5. Practical Preparations\n- Learn basic Spanish\n- Get health insurance\n- Pack appropriate clothing\n- Bring necessary medications\n- Have copies of important documents\n\n6. Safety\n- Research safe neighborhoods\n- Be aware of surroundings\n- Keep valuables secure\n- Follow local guidelines\n\n7. Daily Needs\n- Find local grocery stores\n- Locate healthcare facilities\n- Know emergency contact numbers\n- Have a working phone plan\n\nPreparation and research will help ensure a smooth month-long stay in Tijuana.",
